{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Up2PUUdJByquqLwJBZhBza","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→description: Start autonomous execution — run one sprint in the current session, iterating through stories using BMAD workflows.\n     3→---\n     4→\n     5→# Harness Run — In-Session Sprint Execution\n     6→\n     7→Execute stories autonomously in the current Claude Code session. Reads sprint-status.yaml, iterates through stories using BMAD workflows (create-story → dev-story → code-review → verify), and updates status after each story. This is the single source of sprint execution logic.\n     8→\n     9→> **MANDATORY — Never skip or shortcut verification.**\n    10→> Process stories one at a time, in order. Verification (Step 3d) is the entire point of codeharness — it catches real bugs. If there are 50 stories at `verifying`, verify them one by one. Each verification may surface issues that need fixing — that is the job. Never ask the user to batch-transition statuses, never propose \"lighter\" verification, never skip showboat proofs. If context window is a concern, that is why Ralph loop exists — each session handles a few stories, then a fresh session continues. Do not question, negotiate, or offer alternatives to the process defined below.\n    11→\n    12→## Step 1: Pre-flight — Read Sprint Status\n    13→\n    14→Read the sprint status file to understand current state.\n    15→\n    16→1. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml` in full.\n    17→2. Parse the `development_status` section. Each entry is one of:\n    18→   - **Epic entry:** key matching `epic-N` (e.g., `epic-1`) — status is `backlog`, `in-progress`, or `done`\n    19→   - **Story entry:** key matching `N-M-slug` (e.g., `1-2-user-auth`) — status is `backlog`, `ready-for-dev`, `in-progress`, `review`, `verifying`, or `done`\n    20→   - **Retrospective entry:** key matching `epic-N-retrospective` — status is `optional` or `done`\n    21→3. If the file doesn't exist or has no `development_status`, HALT:\n    22→   ```\n    23→   [FAIL] No sprint-status.yaml found. Run /sprint-planning first.\n    24→   ```\n    25→\n    26→Initialize tracking variables (once, before the loop):\n    27→- `stories_completed = 0`\n    28→- `stories_failed = 0`\n    29→- `stories_skipped = 0`\n    30→- `skipped_reasons = []` (list of `{story_key}: {reason}` strings)\n    31→- `attempts = 0` (per story, resets for each new story — counts ALL retries: dev failures, review round-trips, verify→dev loops)\n    32→- `max_attempts = 10` (single limit for all retry types)\n    33→- `start_time = current timestamp`\n    34→\n    35→## Step 2: Find Next Actionable Story (Cross-Epic Scan)\n    36→\n    37→Scan ALL stories across ALL epics to find the highest-priority actionable story. Epic boundaries do not constrain selection.\n    38→\n    39→1. **Collect all stories:** Gather every `N-M-slug` entry from `development_status`, regardless of which epic it belongs to.\n    40→\n    41→2. **Filter out non-actionable stories.** Remove any story that matches ANY of these conditions:\n    42→   - Status is `done`\n    43→   - **Retry-exhausted:** Read `ralph/.story_retries`. If a line `{story_key}={count}` exists and `count >= max_attempts` (10), the story is retry-exhausted. Increment `stories_skipped`, append `{story_key}: retry-exhausted ({count}/{max_attempts})` to `skipped_reasons`, and print:\n    44→     ```\n    45→     [INFO] Skipping {story_key}: retry-exhausted ({count}/{max_attempts})\n    46→     ```\n    47→   - **Blocked (escalated):** A `verifying` story that already has a proof document (`verification/{story_key}-proof.md` exists) with `escalated > 0` and `pending === 0` is blocked. Increment `stories_skipped`, append `{story_key}: blocked (escalated ACs)` to `skipped_reasons`, and print:\n    48→     ```\n    49→     [INFO] Skipping {story_key}: blocked (escalated ACs)\n    50→     ```\n    51→\n    52→3. **Prioritize remaining stories.** Sort actionable stories into priority tiers (process highest tier first, file order within each tier):\n    53→   - **Tier A — Proof exists, needs validation:** Status is `verifying` AND `verification/{story_key}-proof.md` exists (but story is not blocked per step 2). These are quick wins — just need validation.\n    54→   - **Tier B — In-progress or review:** Status is `in-progress` or `review`. Resume partially-completed work.\n    55→   - **Tier C — Verifying without proof:** Status is `verifying` AND no proof document exists. Needs full Docker verification.\n    56→   - **Tier D — Backlog/ready-for-dev:** Status is `backlog` or `ready-for-dev`. New work.\n    57→\n    58→4. **Select the first story from the prioritized list.** If the list is empty (no actionable stories remain anywhere), go to Step 7 with result `NO_WORK`.\n    59→\n    60→5. **Determine the story's parent epic** (epic number N from the story key `N-M-slug`).\n    61→\n    62→6. **Reset per-story counter:** Set `attempts = 0` for the new story. (Note: if the story has persisted retry state in `ralph/.story_retries` that is below `max_attempts`, read that count and set `attempts` accordingly — this ensures retry budgets persist across sessions.)\n    63→\n    64→7. Print the plan:\n    65→   ```\n    66→   [INFO] Next story: {story_key} (status: {current_status}, tier: {A|B|C|D})\n    67→   [INFO] Parent epic: Epic {N}\n    68→   [INFO] Stories in epic: {done_count}/{total_count} done\n    69→   ```\n    70→\n    71→## Subagent Mandatory Report Sections\n    72→\n    73→Every subagent (create-story, dev-story, code-review, verifier, retrospective) MUST end its response with TWO sections:\n    74→\n    75→### 1. Session Issues\n    76→\n    77→A `## Session Issues` section reporting problems, workarounds, suboptimal outcomes, and observations — not just success/failure status.\n    78→\n    79→### 2. Token Usage Report\n    80→\n    81→A `## Token Report` section with tool call breakdown for cost analysis:\n    82→\n    83→```markdown\n    84→## Token Report\n    85→- Total tool calls: N\n    86→- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, Glob: U, Agent: T\n    87→- Largest Bash outputs: \"{command}\" (~N lines), \"{command}\" (~N lines)\n    88→- Files read: N unique files, M total read calls (list files read 3+ times)\n    89→- Redundant operations: {describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or unnecessary calls}\n    90→```\n    91→\n    92→**After each subagent returns**, extract BOTH sections and append to the session issues log file at `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md`. Use the following format:\n    93→\n    94→```markdown\n    95→### {story_key} — {step name} ({timestamp})\n    96→\n    97→{extracted issues from subagent response}\n    98→\n    99→{extracted token report from subagent response}\n   100→```"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KTsf5fpoa7X5mTtM1qbqAV","session_id":"52ba63bf-4b91-451c-9abd-97fbda8291b9","uuid":"7b75e826-a80e-4808-978d-575456b565b4","timestamp":"2026-03-28T10:54:00.813Z"}
