{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WncpS5juoXqZLrDjnRZHMV","type":"tool_result","content":"   400→7. If any non-escalated ACs were dispatched via the environment-provable path, run cleanup (step 3d-viii) to remove Docker containers and temp workspaces.\n   401→\n   402→**environment-provable verification (derived tier = environment-provable):** Full Docker container with no source code access.\n   403→\n   404→**No internal timeout.** Verification takes as long as it takes. Ralph's iteration timeout is the safety net.\n   405→\n   406→**Pre-verification: Read retry state from `ralph/.story_retries`.**\n   407→\n   408→Read the file `ralph/.story_retries`. If the file contains a line matching `{story_key}={N}`, set `attempts = N`. If no matching line exists, set `attempts = 0`. This ensures retry budgets persist across sessions.\n   409→\n   410→**Pre-verification: Check observability infrastructure.**\n   411→\n   412→```bash\n   413→codeharness status --check-docker 2>&1\n   414→```\n   415→\n   416→If the output indicates the observability stack is down:\n   417→```bash\n   418→codeharness stack start 2>&1\n   419→```\n   420→\n   421→If `codeharness stack start` fails, log `[FAIL] Observability stack failed to start — cannot verify` and go to Step 6 (failure handling).\n   422→\n   423→**Pre-verification: Build dist/.**\n   424→\n   425→```bash\n   426→npm run build 2>&1\n   427→```\n   428→\n   429→If the build fails, fix errors before proceeding. The Docker image needs current dist/.\n   430→\n   431→**Verification flow — execute these steps sequentially:**\n   432→\n   433→**3d-i: Build Docker verify image**\n   434→\n   435→```bash\n   436→codeharness verify-env build 2>&1\n   437→```\n   438→\n   439→If this fails:\n   440→```\n   441→[FAIL] verify-env build failed: {error}\n   442→```\n   443→Leave story at `verifying`, go to Step 6. No fallback.\n   444→\n   445→**3d-ii: Start Docker container**\n   446→\n   447→```bash\n   448→docker run -d --name codeharness-verify --network host \\\n   449→  -e ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=\"$ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\" \\\n   450→  codeharness-verify sleep infinity\n   451→```\n   452→\n   453→`--network host` allows the container to reach OTEL Collector at `localhost:4318`, VictoriaLogs at `:9428`, VictoriaMetrics at `:8428`, and VictoriaTraces at `:16686`. The `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` env var enables the `claude` CLI inside the container for verifier sessions that need to spawn Claude subprocesses.\n   454→\n   455→If `docker run` fails, log `[FAIL] docker run failed: {error}`, leave story at `verifying`, and go to Step 6. No cleanup needed — the container never started.\n   456→\n   457→**3d-iii: Prepare clean workspace**\n   458→\n   459→```bash\n   460→codeharness verify-env prepare --story {story_key} 2>&1\n   461→```\n   462→\n   463→This creates `/tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key}` with built artifacts, docs, and story file — but NO source code.\n   464→\n   465→If this fails, log `[FAIL] verify-env prepare failed: {error}`, leave story at `verifying`, and go to cleanup (step 3d-viii) then Step 6. The container is running and must be cleaned up.\n   466→\n   467→**3d-iv: Run verifier session**\n   468→\n   469→Build the verification prompt and spawn the verifier:\n   470→\n   471→1. Read the story content from `/tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key}/story.md`\n   472→2. Read the prompt template from `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` — use `verifyPromptTemplate()` with the story content, container name `codeharness-verify`, and default observability endpoints\n   473→3. Run the verifier:\n   474→\n   475→```bash\n   476→cd /tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key} && claude --print --max-budget-usd 5 --allowedTools Bash Read Write Glob Grep Edit -p \"{verification_prompt}\"\n   477→```\n   478→\n   479→The prompt (from `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts`) instructs the verifier that:\n   480→\n   481→- It has **NO source code access** — `src/` does not exist in the workspace\n   482→- **ALL CLI commands** must run via `docker exec codeharness-verify <command>`\n   483→- It should read `README.md` for usage guidance\n   484→- It should query observability endpoints from the host:\n   485→  - VictoriaLogs: `http://localhost:9428`\n   486→  - VictoriaMetrics: `http://localhost:8428`\n   487→  - VictoriaTraces: `http://localhost:16686`\n   488→- The proof document goes in `verification/{story_key}-proof.md` within the clean workspace\n   489→- REAL failures must be reported — never fabricate evidence\n   490→- ACs that cannot be verified should be marked `[ESCALATE]`\n   491→\n   492→If the verifier process exits non-zero or times out, treat as failure (proceed to retry logic in step 3d-vii).\n   493→\n   494→**3d-v: Copy proof document back**\n   495→\n   496→```bash\n   497→cp /tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key}/verification/{story_key}-proof.md verification/\n   498→```\n   499→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KTsf5fpoa7X5mTtM1qbqAV","session_id":"52ba63bf-4b91-451c-9abd-97fbda8291b9","uuid":"da2e5a26-d260-4142-aa90-093d7c7861f8","timestamp":"2026-03-28T10:54:07.410Z"}
