{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01WTDX6q4nS5XdTqiDudJKJu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01EBAXGNYXyQZ1dbPxMLVXFw","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/commands/harness-run.md","offset":499,"limit":100},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3772,"cache_read_input_tokens":39797,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3772,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":71,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KTsf5fpoa7X5mTtM1qbqAV","session_id":"52ba63bf-4b91-451c-9abd-97fbda8291b9","uuid":"8a02d9dc-171a-4224-9256-64cf82c84d77"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EBAXGNYXyQZ1dbPxMLVXFw","type":"tool_result","content":"   499→\n   500→If the proof file does not exist (verifier crashed or failed to produce one), treat as failure (step 3d-vii).\n   501→\n   502→**3d-vi: Validate proof quality**\n   503→\n   504→```bash\n   505→codeharness verify --story {story_key} 2>&1\n   506→```\n   507→\n   508→Parse the output/exit code. After parsing each AC verdict from the proof, update the live progress:\n   509→\n   510→```bash\n   511→codeharness progress --ac-progress \"{passed}/{total}\"\n   512→```\n   513→\n   514→where `passed` is ACs with PASS verdict and `total` is all ACs.\n   515→\n   516→- If `pending === 0` and `escalated === 0` → proof quality passed. Update sprint-status.yaml: change `{story_key}` status to `done`. Print: `[OK] Story {story_key}: verifying → done`. Proceed to cleanup (step 3d-viii).\n   517→- If `escalated > 0` and `pending === 0` → verifier could not reach some ACs. **Before accepting escalation, diagnose WHY:**\n   518→  1. Read the proof document. For each `[ESCALATE]` AC, check the reason.\n   519→  2. **If the reason is infrastructure/tooling** (container missing binary, tree-shaking, Docker not configured, wrong version installed): this is NOT a valid escalation. The infrastructure needs fixing. Treat as **Path C** below.\n   520→  3. **If the reason is genuinely impossible to automate** (requires physical hardware, paid external service, human visual judgment): accept the escalation. Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key} has {N} genuinely escalated ACs — marking done with known limitations`. Update status to `done`.\n   521→  4. **Do NOT leave stories at `verifying` with escalated ACs.** Either fix the infra problem (Path C) or accept and mark done.\n   522→- If `pending > 0` → proof has gaps. Treat as failure (step 3d-vii).\n   523→\n   524→If the verifier made code fixes (detected by checking `git diff` after verification), run:\n   525→```bash\n   526→npm run build && npm run test:unit\n   527→```\n   528→to confirm fixes haven't broken anything. Then proceed to cleanup (step 3d-viii).\n   529→\n   530→**3d-vii: Failure handling — code bugs vs infrastructure failures**\n   531→\n   532→Determine the failure type. There are two distinct paths:\n   533→\n   534→**Path A — Code bugs (`pending > 0` in proof validation):**\n   535→\n   536→A proof document exists and `codeharness verify` reported `pending > 0`. This means the feature has real bugs — the code does not satisfy the ACs. Code bugs NEVER count against the retry budget.\n   537→\n   538→1. **Extract failing ACs from the proof document.** Read `verification/{story_key}-proof.md`. For each AC section (`## AC N: description`), check if the verdict is not PASS and not `[ESCALATE]`. For each failing AC, extract:\n   539→   - The AC number and description (from the `## AC N:` heading)\n   540→   - The error output (from the `output` code blocks and any verdict text)\n   541→\n   542→2. **Save findings to the story file.** Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/{story_key}.md`. If it already has a `## Verification Findings` section, replace that section entirely with the new findings. If not, append a new `## Verification Findings` section before the `## Dev Agent Record` section (or at the end if that section doesn't exist). Format:\n   543→   ```markdown\n   544→   ## Verification Findings\n   545→\n   546→   _Last updated: {timestamp}_\n   547→\n   548→   The following ACs failed verification:\n   549→\n   550→   ### AC {N}: {description}\n   551→   **Verdict:** FAIL\n   552→   **Error output:**\n   553→   ```\n   554→   {relevant error output from proof}\n   555→   ```\n   556→\n   557→   {repeat for each failing AC}\n   558→   ```\n   559→\n   560→3. **Increment `attempts`.** If `attempts >= max_attempts` (10):\n   561→   - Increment `stories_skipped`\n   562→   - Append `{story_key}: verify↔dev cycle limit (10)` to `skipped_reasons`\n   563→   - Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key}: verify↔dev cycle limit reached — skipping`\n   564→   - Run cleanup (step 3d-viii)\n   565→   - Go to Step 2 (next story)\n   566→\n   567→4. **Return story to dev.** Update sprint-status.yaml: change `{story_key}` status from `verifying` to `in-progress`.\n   568→\n   569→5. **Reset retry count.** Update `ralph/.story_retries`: write/replace the line `{story_key}=0` in the file (read existing file first to preserve other entries). This resets the infra retry budget since the story is going back to dev.\n   570→\n   571→6. Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key}: verification found {N} failing ACs — returning to dev (attempt {attempts}/{max_attempts})`\n   572→\n   573→7. Run cleanup (step 3d-viii).\n   574→\n   575→8. Go to Step 3b (dev-story) — the story is now `in-progress` and the dev prompt will include the verification findings.\n   576→\n   577→**Path B — Infrastructure failures (timeout, docker error, no proof produced, verifier non-zero exit WITHOUT a proof):**\n   578→\n   579→The verification could not complete due to infrastructure issues — NOT code quality.\n   580→\n   581→**Before retrying blindly, diagnose the infra problem:**\n   582→\n   583→1. Read the verifier output/error. Identify what specifically failed:\n   584→   - Container missing the project binary? → Fix `Dockerfile.verify` or `verify-env prepare` to install it correctly\n   585→   - Tree-shaking removed needed code from dist/? → Add the entry point to tsup config or create a CLI command that exposes the functionality\n   586→   - Wrong version of tool in container? → Fix the Docker image build to use local dist/\n   587→   - Port conflict? → Fix shared stack detection\n   588→   - Container didn't start? → Fix Docker configuration\n   589→\n   590→2. **Fix the infrastructure problem** by modifying the relevant files (Dockerfile, verify-env, tsup config, docker-compose). This is a code change — commit it.\n   591→\n   592→3. Rebuild: `npm run build`\n   593→\n   594→4. Retry verification with the fixed infrastructure.\n   595→\n   596→5. If after 3 infra fix attempts the problem persists, increment `attempts` and move to next story:\n   597→   - Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key}: infra problem persists after 3 fix attempts — skipping (attempt {attempts}/{max_attempts})`\n   598→   - Go to Step 2"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KTsf5fpoa7X5mTtM1qbqAV","session_id":"52ba63bf-4b91-451c-9abd-97fbda8291b9","uuid":"c86f25fc-583f-4cd5-aff9-d195c998eea9","timestamp":"2026-03-28T10:54:11.139Z"}
