{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XmBjz1MbfE486DZueVjr2i","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DpznMoA3m476pSD6FhHLDa","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/commands/harness-run.md","offset":598,"limit":100},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2040,"cache_read_input_tokens":43569,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2040,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":71,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KTsf5fpoa7X5mTtM1qbqAV","session_id":"52ba63bf-4b91-451c-9abd-97fbda8291b9","uuid":"9e9c09ce-c00b-4120-86be-b9444b817581"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DpznMoA3m476pSD6FhHLDa","type":"tool_result","content":"   598→   - Go to Step 2\n   599→\n   600→**The agent must NOT repeatedly retry the same broken infrastructure.** Each retry must include an actual fix attempt.\n   601→\n   602→**Path C — Escalated ACs due to infra/tooling problems:**\n   603→\n   604→An AC was marked `[ESCALATE]` but the reason is infrastructure, not impossibility. Fix the infrastructure:\n   605→\n   606→1. Identify the infra problem from the escalation reason (container missing binary, tree-shaking, Docker config, etc.)\n   607→2. Fix the root cause — modify Dockerfile, tsup config, verify-env, or whatever is broken\n   608→3. Delete the existing proof: `rm verification/{story_key}-proof.md`\n   609→4. Return story to `verifying` and re-run verification from step 3d-i\n   610→5. Do NOT accept infra problems as valid escalations\n   611→\n   612→**3d-viii: Cleanup (unconditional — runs on both success and failure)**\n   613→\n   614→```bash\n   615→codeharness verify-env cleanup --story {story_key} 2>&1\n   616→```\n   617→\n   618→This removes the temp workspace at `/tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key}` and stops/removes the Docker container. This step MUST run even if verification failed — leaked containers and temp directories accumulate.\n   619→\n   620→If cleanup fails, log a warning but continue:\n   621→```\n   622→[WARN] verify-env cleanup failed for {story_key}: {error}\n   623→```\n   624→\n   625→### 3e: Sync Beads Status\n   626→\n   627→After the story reaches `done`, sync the status to beads (if initialized):\n   628→\n   629→```bash\n   630→codeharness sync --story {story_key} --direction files-to-beads\n   631→```\n   632→\n   633→If this fails, log a warning but continue — beads sync is not a blocking step:\n   634→```\n   635→[WARN] Beads sync failed for {story_key}: {error message}\n   636→```\n   637→\n   638→### 3f: Commit Story Changes\n   639→\n   640→After the story reaches `done`, commit all changes with a coherent message.\n   641→\n   642→1. Stage all changes: `git add -A`\n   643→2. Commit with message: `feat: story {story_key} — {short title from story file}`\n   644→3. The commit must include source code, tests, story file, sprint-status.yaml, proof document, and any other changed files\n   645→4. If `git commit` fails (e.g., pre-commit hooks), log the error and continue — do not halt the sprint:\n   646→   ```\n   647→   [WARN] git commit failed for story {story_key}: {error message}\n   648→   ```\n   649→\n   650→## Step 4: Story Complete — Continue or Finish Epic\n   651→\n   652→A story just completed successfully. Clear live run progress immediately:\n   653→\n   654→```bash\n   655→codeharness progress --clear\n   656→```\n   657→\n   658→1. Increment `stories_completed`\n   659→2. Re-read `sprint-status.yaml` to get current state\n   660→3. Determine the story's parent epic (epic number N from the story key)\n   661→4. Check if all stories in epic N are `done` (every `N-M-slug` has status `done`):\n   662→   - If yes → go to Step 5 (epic completion). After Step 5, return to Step 2 for the next cross-epic scan.\n   663→   - If no → go directly to Step 2 for the next cross-epic scan (attempts will be reset there for the new story)\n   664→\n   665→## Step 5: Epic Completion\n   666→\n   667→All stories in the current epic are done.\n   668→\n   669→1. Check if `epic-{N}-retrospective` entry exists and status is `optional`:\n   670→   - If yes, run the retrospective:\n   671→     ```\n   672→     Use the Agent tool with:\n   673→       prompt: \"Run /retrospective for Epic {N}. All stories are complete. Review the epic's work, extract lessons learned, and produce the retrospective document. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n   674→\n   675→MANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n   676→- Epic-level problems (recurring patterns across stories, process breakdowns)\n   677→- Stories that were harder than expected and why\n   678→- Action items that need immediate attention vs. backlog\n   679→- Process improvements that should be encoded in tooling/config, not just documented\n   680→If nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n   681→\n   682→MANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n   683→- Total tool calls: N\n   684→- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n   685→- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n   686→- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n   687→- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls\"\n   688→       subagent_type: \"general-purpose\"\n   689→     ```\n   690→   - After retrospective completes:\n   691→     a. Update `epic-{N}-retrospective` status to `done` in sprint-status.yaml (use Edit tool — do NOT rely on the retro agent to do this)\n   692→     b. Verify the update was applied\n   693→\n   694→2. Update `epic-{N}` status to `done` in sprint-status.yaml (use Edit tool)\n   695→\n   696→3. Commit epic completion: `git add -A && git commit -m \"feat: epic {N} complete\"`\n   697→   - If `git commit` fails, log the error and continue:"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KTsf5fpoa7X5mTtM1qbqAV","session_id":"52ba63bf-4b91-451c-9abd-97fbda8291b9","uuid":"d41ed834-8dbd-4257-a688-573001b1c7de","timestamp":"2026-03-28T10:54:14.242Z"}
