{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KTsf5fpoa7X5mTtM1qbqAV","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** 16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch\n**Git vs Story Discrepancies:** 0 found\n**Issues Found:** 0 High, 3 Medium (all fixed), 2 Low (not fixed)\n\n**MEDIUM ISSUES (FIXED):**\n\n1. **No indexOf guard — silent false positives on section extraction** — 8 instances of `content.indexOf(...)` used without checking for -1. If a section header were renamed, `slice(-1, nextEnd)` would return most of the file, and assertions like `not.toContain` could silently pass on wrong content. **Fixed:** Added `extractSection()` helper that throws on missing headers.\n\n2. **DRY violation — repeated section extraction** — The same `indexOf`/`slice` pattern was copy-pasted 8 times across AC2, AC3, and AC5 tests (3 times each for AC3 and AC5). **Fixed:** Introduced `extractSection()` helper and per-describe lazy accessors (`runtimeSection()`, `escalateSection()`).\n\n3. **Fragile section boundary coupling** — Tests depended on implicit document ordering with no safety net if order changed. **Fixed:** Same `extractSection()` helper with explicit error messages identifies exactly which header is missing.\n\n**LOW ISSUES (NOT FIXED):**\n\n1. **Routing table order vs section order mismatch** — The dispatch routing table (L280-283) lists tiers in TIER_HIERARCHY order (test→runtime→environment→escalate), but the actual sections appear as test→runtime→escalate→environment. The current order has a reasonable justification (escalate references environment-provable as a sub-dispatch), and the routing table explicitly names the target section, so an LLM can follow it. Cosmetic only.\n\n2. **Tests are purely string-matching against markdown** — All 34 tests use `toContain`/`not.toContain` on raw markdown content. This is appropriate for a prompt-engineering story (no TypeScript code changes), but these tests are inherently brittle — any wording change breaks them. This is a known limitation documented in the story's dev notes.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Bugs found:** 0 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM (all fixed — indexOf guard, DRY violation, fragile section coupling), 2 LOW (not fixed — section ordering, string-matching test brittleness)\n- **Code quality issues found but NOT fixed:** LOW — routing table vs section order mismatch in harness-run.md; string-matching test brittleness (inherent to testing prompt files)\n- **Coverage gaps:** None. All 158 files above 80% floor, overall 96.85% > 90% target.\n- **Architecture concerns:** None. The four-tier dispatch correctly mirrors TIER_HIERARCHY from types.ts. LEGACY_TIER_MAP entries in the prompt match the TypeScript constants.\n- **Items sent back for re-development:** None.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 27\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 10, Edit: 5, Grep: 8, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx codeharness coverage` (~5 lines), `npx vitest run` (~5 lines), `git log --oneline` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 13 total reads (harness-run.md read 5 times via offset/limit chunking, harness-run-dispatch.test.ts read 2 times)\n- Redundant operations: harness-run-dispatch.test.ts was read twice (once full for review, once to confirm before editing — second read was necessary to see final state before edits). Coverage command run twice (before/after fixes — both necessary)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2a7e3c8e7e8fc22f (use SendMessage with to: 'a2a7e3c8e7e8fc22f' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 70240\ntool_uses: 47\nduration_ms: 276309</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"52ba63bf-4b91-451c-9abd-97fbda8291b9","uuid":"a5e5469d-800a-4d27-aef7-e9b916f6d73e","timestamp":"2026-03-28T10:57:56.805Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verific