{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01K8HDEaYE5cEXgnvtVhEuYG","type":"tool_result","content":"269:**Step 3d-0: Read the story file and derive the verification tier from AC-level tags.**\n275:Parse ALL lines in the Acceptance Criteria section. For each AC, extract its `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag (if present). Map any legacy tag values via `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`: `cli-verifiable` → `test-provable`, `integration-required` → `environment-provable`, `unit-testable` → `test-provable`, `black-box` → `environment-provable`. Collect all parsed tiers into an array.\n277:Compute the story's derived tier: `maxTier(collectedTiers)`. If no AC-level tags are found at all, default to `test-provable`.\n280:- **`test-provable`** → Use **test-provable verification** (below). No Docker, no running the app.\n281:- **`runtime-provable`** → Use **runtime-provable verification** (below). Build and run the app locally — no Docker stack.\n282:- **`environment-provable`** → Use **environment-provable verification** (below). Full Docker flow.\n283:- **`escalate`** → Use **escalate verification** (below). Mixed-tier dispatch per AC.\n285:**test-provable verification (derived tier = test-provable):**\n333:**runtime-provable verification (derived tier = runtime-provable):**\n386:**escalate verification (derived tier = escalate):**\n390:1. Re-read the story file. For each AC, extract its individual `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag (with legacy mapping as in Step 3d-0).\n392:   - `escalate`-tier ACs: mark each as `[ESCALATE]` in the proof document with the reason \"Requires human judgment or external service — cannot be automated.\"\n396:   - `[ESCALATE]` verdict for each escalated AC (with reason)\n402:**environment-provable verification (derived tier = environment-provable):** Full Docker container with no source code access.\n490:- ACs that cannot be verified should be marked `[ESCALATE]`\n518:  1. Read the proof document. For each `[ESCALATE]` AC, check the reason.\n538:1. **Extract failing ACs from the proof document.** Read `verification/{story_key}-proof.md`. For each AC section (`## AC N: description`), check if the verdict is not PASS and not `[ESCALATE]`. For each failing AC, extract:\n604:An AC was marked `[ESCALATE]` but the reason is infrastructure, not impossibility. Fix the infrastructure:\n818:     * Stories that should use test-provable verification instead of Docker"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Wa132g8zaHfTf7e2yDXVpx","session_id":"52ba63bf-4b91-451c-9abd-97fbda8291b9","uuid":"77a38252-175a-41e8-bc3b-25cf25ed357f","timestamp":"2026-03-28T11:07:34.129Z"}
